We were absolutely not disappointed. Our server was amazing! The food spectacular, and the atmosphere appropriate for the Emerald City!
Living in Bonney Lake and pretty much giving up on Seattle... King County... and all of the uncontrolled nonsense. This was the first time I have not been to this area since the pre-Pandemic, pre-Riots, and pre-Waterfront rejuvenation.

We are impressed at the way that this area around Pikes Place is visibly beginning to turn the corner and become something better than it was before.', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [], 'tags': []}, {'position': 6, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-24T10:19:11Z', 'user': {'name': 'Matthew M.', 'user_id': 'I9WabQPpBg66lwWpaxtpJQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=I9WabQPpBg66lwWpaxtpJQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/6SJVko9c4zDYTmXAbSZi5Q/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Gardena, CA', 'friends': 248, 'photos': 35, 'reviews': 31, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Let me start off by saying, this was the #1 recommended spots for us to try out in Seattle.. it didn't disappoint me. Service was phenomenal from our server, to the gentleman refilling our glasses. Service is huge to me coming back to an establishment.. y'all did it. Ambiance was very nice, loved the fact there were tables looking out into Seattle. Food, was good, nothing amazing but it was good. I'm more impressed with the service given to us that night compared to the food, if I'm being honest. Overall, I'd come back for the service and ambiance, food wont compare to those in Los Angeles, but it's good for what I was expecting. 

Much love!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ecuwCkemxEr238Xh0Db1cw/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/W6i4HHtFXwEE_Y-8WYTaOQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/xSP5rMS2YdDK3sAUAe0dZA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/qXV45O-uGfAcg3LRjeBA7A/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['4 photos']}, {'position': 7, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-16T01:53:27Z', 'user': {'name': 'Tiffany T.', 'user_id': 'yadkBInjtUEAofYuq3rJdQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=yadkBInjtUEAofYuq3rJdQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/CmBFgpp_kSOJHdfHq8HZIw/180s.jpg', 'address': 'VA, VA', 'friends': 34, 'photos': 1045, 'reviews': 270, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "We didn't have a reservation but put our names down and got lucky around 15-30 minutes later they were able to seat our group of 4. It's literally just a pink door outside so look for the pink door with no sign to find it! Inside has a nice vibe and they play live music too. It's dim inside and can be romantic or just kinda chill depending on who you're with. 

I forgot what drink I got but it had a sweet dried fig on top and was a warm cocktail! I never had a warm cocktail so that was pretty unique. pretty strong but balanced by the toppings 3/5

Forgot what my partner got too but i liked his as well. more like a standard fruity drink in a cute glass. 

Oysters - good! flavorful and fresh. 3/5

Linguine Alle Vongole -  A little unmemorable. I think it was a little bland? 2.5/5

parpardelle al ragu - i really liked the texture of the pasta. Homemade, soft and bouncy a bit. Good sauce too. 3.75/5

Squid ink pasta - a little salty but good. 2.75/5", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/BYfZ2ek8B4MaJVlDTKl8Zw/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/WYKbo58tpmZDzqeknlm1hw/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/0ntq_T6kD4rOu1W98y2edA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/j1NTZD5HdKLbn8E9bnpyNQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/aPEhA1wSrBspJ69rLdG3QQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/SFV5f9bBHJITIXUTTk1uYg/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/PFKqyqLWlXj3YjXciwEESA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/WQxWkumvgafLU9RxRVbUaA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/DubuA5BD26nFmFyZ-QvHOA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/XM-JoNy6AfIblpC4De86ow/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['10 photos']}, {'position': 8, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-04T21:04:38Z', 'user': {'name': 'Sabrina L.', 'user_id': '9WjhcepzsT1UHrwqCr-yCQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=9WjhcepzsT1UHrwqCr-yCQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/RzYuCi6CvS0L4Bfg2s3xdw/180s.jpg', 'address': 'San Jose, CA', 'friends': 14, 'photos': 460, 'reviews': 98, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': 'Hidden treasure -- a cute pink door towards taste bud feast. Walked into the door , stairs down into a classy Italian dinning atmosphere, lovely. 
Knowing this restaurant is popular, ran there around there during opening time, fortunately got one of the last three bar seats. The bartender is friendly and kind, and took his recommendations on the dishes, turned out brilliant choices -- the most impressive one is the lasagna, reminded me of how food really tastes in Italy. Although cheesy but not greasy. Each layer has its flavor, harmony on the mixture. Another highlight is the bread and olive oil ( must must try) . 
The dish portion is not big, which is good for more dishes to try. Love each dish ordered. Highly recommended!', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/cxdSuumr--kbajFcWuhbcA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Arancini'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/KbC7fl1-Mrc7N9mFTnSiSw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Menu'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/qyJDGczGSzx6aK4WEyT1kw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Lasagna Pink Door -- delicious'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/wx1nHdpqffKndVivDLxZwA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Carrots'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/WqzLQvbyaJU-c-mX0HyxrA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Generous clam linguine'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/H_PM5CH2KfiG6kkoRk9oLg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Lemon tart'}], 'tags': ['6 photos']}, {'position': 9, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-05-05T18:26:17Z', 'user': {'name': 'Jennifer G.', 'user_id': 'mob2OCkgZ0NCXdbw6GVXIQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=mob2OCkgZ0NCXdbw6GVXIQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/AchIZcv_dPqMqBNkF06Q_Q/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Los Angeles, CA', 'friends': 92, 'photos': 442, 'reviews': 160, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': 'Wonderful place the aesthetics of this Italian restaurant was wonderful. reviews_data:
[{'position': 1, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-03-30T18:17:13Z', 'user': {'name': 'Rosemary Z.', 'user_id': 'OQ7iYUbyuoQ_DJluyO8ZkQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=OQ7iYUbyuoQ_DJluyO8ZkQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/k0gTEFep7h047pW9UJU9uw/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 0, 'photos': 2, 'reviews': 1, 'elite_year': 0}, 'comment': {'text': 'Ube pancake is the goat. Great service and vibe. Love this place and will definitely visit again in the future.', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/8bWA_DFGgHFEYA6ix679Qg/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/0ke0JPZ2-_fUTUEGckYqFw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Ube pancake'}], 'tags': ['2 photos']}, {'position': 2, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-05-04T18:30:10Z', 'user': {'name': 'Tim M.', 'user_id': 'rqAneVbPEBkK3YM0BWPFkg', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=rqAneVbPEBkK3YM0BWPFkg', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/a0PUVFc0zHMZ1YJFe4k8Wg/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 447, 'photos': 65, 'reviews': 64, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Spoiler alert: you will food coma afterwards XD

Ludi's has been on my list of places to check out for a while and it did not disappoint! I came here Saturday morning around 10am and there was a decent sized line (waited about 30 minutes to get inside). When you enter, you order at the counter and then are seated by the staff so no worries about needing to stand around for an empty table.

I ordered the lechón and split the ube pancakes with my friends. Ube pancakes - so so good! Spongy texture, perfect for absorbing the sauce which is strong with both ube and coconut notes (not muted at all). The lechón - so crispy, juicy, all around yummy haha! The sauce it comes with helps cut through the fattiness and adds a little bit of sweetness to keep things interesting. 

Would definitely come again to try out their other dishes. Some tips - ube pancakes are on the sweeter side so better to split with someone or only order a single if you only want to try. Also I heard that weekdays aren't nearly as crowded if you don't want to wait around in line (can also order to-go).", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/V8N_B4LNq5Qxf0MA1H3fsw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Lechón Kawali (fried pork belly)'}], 'tags': ['1 photo', '1 check-in']}, {'position': 3, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-30T22:59:07Z', 'user': {'name': 'Eva H.', 'user_id': 'T96VgWg-gIY6bEC2rFoOzw', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=T96VgWg-gIY6bEC2rFoOzw', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/Q04lhnU1-pBLKZtIdz95bQ/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Brea, CA', 'friends': 15, 'photos': 78, 'reviews': 32, 'elite_year': 0}, 'comment': {'text': "This place is outstanding! 

You want to feel at home? And experience what real customer service is... come here! This is not a commercial but a testimony of how great work these folks have done. Don Tito is the nicest individual you will meet in Seattle. We were in a Business conference and just happened to be nearby this place, of course we were starving and decided to tried it. You won't regret it... Believe me and look at the pictures for some evidence! Thank you for the amazing service! Ambiance is welcoming and food is also great specially the lechon? I think that is the name of the delicious fried meat!! I know fried!! Just try it!! It is worthy it! And just do some cardio afterwards.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/xgN6lu75eS65KTvyVYyReg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Gregorio Rodas aka Tito'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/MPcuDz-ktOJzNMGOdr6W_g/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Z3LEuiVqaXSgCcBNcS6IXg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Decir'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/cyDs0hQd_OON7ez5C62iPg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Inside'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/BCEtdLzMdks1FSEazM9L9A/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/1aU9IoYxUKXPnuq68kdzjw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Coffee'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/jtRmU-ErSmrC38CVDANJMg/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['7 photos']}, {'position': 4, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-23T19:12:28Z', 'user': {'name': 'Andrew Z.', 'user_id': 'nNyjYnbMETNiJyH1aFE1rw', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=nNyjYnbMETNiJyH1aFE1rw', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/uAybMMolQdjsnsuBrMsmYQ/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 188, 'photos': 117, 'reviews': 105, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Ludi's is one of the classic Seattle restaurants that seemingly everyone goes to while visiting around Pike Place, and for good reason. I came with a group on a weekday early morning, and there was surprisingly no wait.

I had the ilocos silos and the ube pancakes. The sausages were tasty and the garlic rice was super good as well! On the side, they also served a sauce (kinda like a pico de gallo?) which I was a huge fan of! The ube pancakes were soft and tasty too.

Overall, I was very happy with Ludis restaurant and I will definitely be trying to come back more often!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/E4hkN2vnoQytCxLL8W6FzQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Ilocos Salog'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/iHz2LbVZxDUnriTfe_AJnw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Ube pancakes'}], 'tags': ['2 photos', '1 check-in']}, {'position': 5, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-22T22:11:07Z', 'user': {'name': 'Rebecca H.', 'user_id': 'AjmMP8bVQYSaAQ-GPr5DZw', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=AjmMP8bVQYSaAQ-GPr5DZw', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/AXQKs_CeThkq9gTHuscC0Q/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Everett, WA', 'friends': 139, 'photos': 155, 'reviews': 65, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "4.5 stars rounded up! 
Ludi's has been on my must try list for so long and I can see what the hype is all about!

I think what really makes Ludi's stand out is its service. I'm usually not a fan of places that make you pay & tip before you sit down, but their service stands out from the moment you enter the restaurant. It feels like a local diner in the middle of the city because of how friendly the service is here. You can tell it's definitely family-oriented and feels like a home-cooked brunch. They offered a little sample of hot chocolate as we waited in line on a cold Saturday morning and everyone seems genuinely happy to be there.

We split a long silog and a stack of their ube pancakes between 2 and it was very filling. The long silog was excellent. The sausages are sweet, but not in a the typical American breakfast fashion. They still pair nicely with a savory breakfast. 

The ube pancakes are reminiscent of a Vietnamese coconut pandan waffle, but I really enjoyed the sauce that covers the pancakes.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/NyWzYcVD5GQHViA4GPXv8A/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['1 photo']}, {'position': 6, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-20T19:36:53Z', 'user': {'name': 'Warren W.', 'user_id': 'kzih6r27F5PBxL2qFFTj3g', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=kzih6r27F5PBxL2qFFTj3g', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/_fCuXI8Y9J3lFQKdjkM3hQ/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Bellevue, WA', 'friends': 1, 'photos': 62, 'reviews': 81, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Plan to be in line for an hour. They open at 7:00 and there was a line at 6:30. We got in line a bit before 11:00 on a Saturday and got in a bit after noon. Once you get to the register, you can pre order your food and then you will be seated. We ordered the full stack of ube pancakes, the lechon kawali, combo silong and lumpia's. The servers were nice and the food came out in 5-10 minutes. 

As expected the food was good. The pork belly had good flavor but on the dryer side. The garlic rice was savory and a great base to the rest of the food. The ube pancake was sweet with a hint of coconut. The sweet pork sausage was one of my favorites. The beef lumpia was good but the veggie lumpia was better. I'll be back when I visit Seattle next.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/PCLBQnD-u4NCJ8gSr-t_bA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['1 photo']}, {'position': 10, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-05-04T09:05:14Z', 'user': {'name': 'Micah E.', 'user_id': '6yiLZMNiT2EgY_OS5EH3HA', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=6yiLZMNiT2EgY_OS5EH3HA', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/V48buBR1Qpr9nkWE73pUuQ/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Cypress, CA', 'friends': 0, 'photos': 22, 'reviews': 56, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "i loved this place!! it's easy for me to think all filipino breakfast is the same as a filipino person, but my boyfriend really wanted us to try ludi's because he loves filipino breakfast! i am so happy we went!! i felt like i was in my own lola's house having breakfast while i was eating at ludi's. the servers were all kind and welcoming throughout our time in the restaurant. all of the pictures around the restaurant of family and other filipino trinkets was so heartwarming. the longanisa and porkchop were my favorites, but i wish i had more room in my stomach to have tried more things! definitely come with an empty stomach when you come to ludi's. :)", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Cmg1vTf5XgSup1zyRCZC8g/o.jpg', 'caption': 'lechon kawali'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Drn0I0Hunq4oodZ-xPHi5A/o.jpg', 'caption': 'longsilog, porkchop (side), lechon-kawali-silog, and lilikoi iced tea.'}], 'tags': ['2 photos']}]

name: Biscuit Bitch
reviews_data:
[{'position': 1, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-08T05:37:49Z', 'user': {'name': 'Rachael J.', 'user_id': 'p0k96ygiuJoBl06KuAOf0A', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=p0k96ygiuJoBl06KuAOf0A', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/AqRq6OhCUvT-chkLMTxoeg/180s.jpg', 'address': 'San Bruno, CA', 'friends': 203, 'photos': 4, 'reviews': 35, 'elite_year': 0}, 'comment': {'text': 'The biscuit was bitching, the meats delicious, and the staff delightful. The ambiance does not disappoint--every sign starts with "BITCH," the food was handed over with a jaunty "thanks, bitch," and the merch is hi-la-ri-ous. According to my partner, the Canadian Bitch was stellar, though it came drenched in honey that our meager napkins were not prepared to handle. But my bitches, I should have been more suspicious of "famous Bitch sauce." My spam/egg/cheese Bitchwich came with a big slathering of some sort of smoky aioli (the aforementioned famous sauce). This would work for some folks, but as a fervent hater of all things mayo (including admittedly slightly less grotesque homemade aiolis like this one), this was an enormous disappointment. I ended up chucking the bottom half of the sandwich and wiping off the contaminated egg, but it's hard to fully dispense with that flavor. 

TL;DR
What they do, they do REALLY well. But read the menu closely lest you miss important information!', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [], 'tags': []}, {'position': 2, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-05-05T00:20:52Z', 'user': {'name': 'Jessica P.', 'user_id': 'kmt0n9x_TAUz0ggj2XoIEQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=kmt0n9x_TAUz0ggj2XoIEQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/xdxs6EHXLoPmEJlL0AhDWg/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Chino, CA', 'friends': 87, 'photos': 831, 'reviews': 294, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "We decided to stop here on the recommendation of a friend. 
You order from a small window (music is loud and obnoxious and the place is chaotic ) and they shout your order back to the cooks. 
We got a bacon b, a sausage b and a couple of plain biscuits for our girls. 
The biscuits: fresh and fluffy and buttery. The breakfast sandwiches come with a savory pink sauce which I wasn't expecting but it wasn't too bad.
Overall the place sort of lived up to the hype taste wise, it's really pretty simple actually. Biscuits are easy to mess up and they seem to have the formula down for a good biscuit. The place, it's just really tiny and a bit annoying to order over loud rap music and from a tiny window. Would I return , likely yes because the biscuits with the honey butter and jam are tasty!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'photos': [], 'tags': []}, {'position': 3, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-04-30T07:43:52Z', 'user': {'name': 'Shirley W.', 'user_id': 'tTaSbpoUoRU9lp-SWaDRHg', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=tTaSbpoUoRU9lp-SWaDRHg', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/LpEo0U6rC8PKfEn7wHDf8w/180s.jpg', 'address': 'San Gabriel, CA', 'friends': 44, 'photos': 1354, 'reviews': 809, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Located near the Pike Place Market. Parking may be difficult to find, but there are several parking structures around the area. 

Should've ordered online in advance because theres a QR code right at the front that makes you order online anyways lol. I'm not from here, but it seemed like people already knew that so they would just come by and wait for their order. Luckily the wait wasn't too long to get my order, about 15 mins? 

There's very limited outdoor seating right by the side, but we were able to snag a table! The employees here are very casual and sassy, they crack jokes with the customers here lol.

I got to try the Gritty Scrambled Bitch and the others got Smokin Hot Bitch. I mainly had the Gritty Scrambled and I thought it was quite nice. It's very filling, but the biscuit goes so well with everything together. The egg was done nicely as well. I rarely have grits, so it was pretty nice to enjoy it overall. Although, I feel like this dish was missing something? Something that could elevate it more, but it seemed like a safe breakfast choice.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 3, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 3}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/gX96-esUz6hg4Y6T1q71rQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Gritty Scrambled Bitch'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/GeZJuEkeqhNRBbHQtaNlNw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Gritty Scrambled & Smokin Hot Bitch'}], 'tags': ['2 photos']}, {'position': 4, 'rating': 3, 'date': '2025-04-26T16:11:45Z', 'user': {'name': 'T H.', 'user_id': '2rqaKFmE9CJegJMQCKS1Pw', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=2rqaKFmE9CJegJMQCKS1Pw', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/bOGeEPvnv5xHq2qdrxVuWw/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Bedford, KY', 'friends': 0, 'photos': 0, 'reviews': 22, 'elite_year': 0}, 'comment': {'text': 'Service was awesome!!!   Upbeat and very friendly.   Ordered the bacon, egg and cheese biscuit.   Biscuit was great, the small portion of the egg was the issue.  For a biscuit that large, it needed more egg to keep the sandwich from being overpowered (Dry).  

We probably would go back, but would try the biscuit and gravy next time.', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [], 'tags': []}, {'position': 5, 'rating': 3, 'date': '2025-04-19T04:58:30Z', 'user': {'name': 'Megan V.', 'user_id': 'dUDOm12lYpKKMks7yhd7Sg', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=dUDOm12lYpKKMks7yhd7Sg', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/fNff8ENfo_HEVkLPF6ceBA/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Phoenix, AZ', 'friends': 61, 'photos': 397, 'reviews': 192, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Love the food but hate the location. We struggled to find a place to sit, and with it being our first time at Biscuit Bitch, we didn't realize that seating was so limited.

As for the food - the gravy was spectacular and added a delightful flavor when paired with the biscuit! But the actual biscuit was okay. Not as flavorful as I had expected and could have used a bit of salt. The sausage was also lacking in flavor on the sandwich, but the sauce definitely helped and I could have used more of it!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/uEcrWL8tNDswbq6pAzDv_Q/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Cheesy Bacon Biscuit and Gravy'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Ahy7YR91V2JrTHeuKRAeWg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Sausage Bitchwich'}], 'tags': ['2 photos']}, {'position': 6, 'rating': 1, 'date': '2025-03-18T03:08:28Z', 'user': {'name': 'Sierra W.', 'user_id': 'ULO9tTrr-J42vpIsjKlFEg', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=ULO9tTrr-J42vpIsjKlFEg', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/8YgLt6elnUWpihneAQDDIw/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 55, 'photos': 804, 'reviews': 169, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Not worth the hype. 

I've tried both locations now throughout the years. My latest experience was at the downtown location and it was a let down. 

Food is mid and gravy was bland and had a weird texture. You can tell the employees really don't want to be there and love calling the customers bitches since they obviously hate the customers. Some outside seating at this location. 

I hadn't been to biscuit bitch in years and decided to give it another try and don't remember them calling you bitches. Honestly didn't like it. Especially because I could tell they were calling me a bitch in not a nice way. Again the employees seemed annoyed and didn't take pride in their work. Food is presented nicely but just doesn't taste good and is way overpriced. I don't leave a lot of bad reviews but sadly I believe Biscuit Bitch is a big miss and skip for me. Plenty of other better breakfast options nearby with better biscuits and gravy.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/qeIZgf-FAX2gkLGYzWK4-w/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/OKo_kHhWyX2u1zGEObj7JQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/9Hs_SebSGjlPM0LFKQ75Cw/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['3 photos']}, {'position': 7, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-04-25T01:49:05Z', 'user': {'name': 'Brian Q.', 'user_id': 'l3V--LeFTiSIm7SZT7Si9g', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=l3V--LeFTiSIm7SZT7Si9g', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/7BfY7wtrNXjUJ_8jgWLCZg/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Artesia, CA', 'friends': 2, 'photos': 316, 'reviews': 170, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Just listening to the workers here call our names for the orders is entertaining in itself, they give you sass but in just a playful enough way. I tried the cheesy pork n' bitch, it was pretty good, but it got a little salty after eating it for a while. The location isn't the best if you're looking to dine in, we had to walk a little bit to find some tables near Pike's Place, which wasn't too bad.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Bq9vGG4od7qRnQZ8UG2VyA/o.jpg', 'caption': "cheesy pork 'n bitch"}], 'tags': ['1 photo', '1 check-in']}, {'position': 8, 'rating': 3, 'date': '2025-03-08T05:15:57Z', 'user': {'name': 'Tiffany P.', 'user_id': 'coPP8fQVpAIdClodL_-sIA', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=coPP8fQVpAIdClodL_-sIA', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/yI5BDNnNElriGTtTer6Yog/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Orange County, CA', 'friends': 40, 'photos': 1609, 'reviews': 497, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "I'll take a biscuit with a side of attitude. The sassy workers are definitely the best part of this restaurant! 

It's not hard to spot this hole-in-the-wall, thanks to the standing crowd of people. Whether you place a mobile order or in-person, prepare yourself for a long wait alongside other hungry patrons. With no private seating of their own, we managed to snag outdoor seats at the adjacent cafe. 

The Straight-Up Bitch (biscuit topped with country sausage gravy) and Bitchwich (buttered biscuit with bacon, egg, and cheese) were simple, freshly made, and filling. Good biscuits, but not great.

Fun vibes but the food isn't quite worth the wait!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 3, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/tHP8ezn6wt-U3DfLc2dIuw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Bitchwich (buttered biscuit with bacon, egg, and cheese)'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/cFHkTyD_7T3Eq5GBp-ge4Q/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Straight-Up Bitch (biscuit topped with country sausage gravy)'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/OWd0-TCo6Gln0hfWi7eVLw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Bitchwich (buttered biscuit with bacon, egg, and cheese)'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/TVSTwi93y1ULWkhkX9j0Tw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Straight-Up Bitch (biscuit topped with country sausage gravy)'}], 'tags': ['4 photos']}, {'position': 9, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-23T23:21:06Z', 'user': {'name': 'Vincent L.', 'user_id': '8_x0yNZDJEaeddZph2rk3A', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=8_x0yNZDJEaeddZph2rk3A', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/vyCtHl2DDgI5n5i17ch3pw/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Gambrills, MD', 'friends': 2, 'photos': 140, 'reviews': 40, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': 'What can I say? I don't know about you,, but it brightened my morning up. The place is small, they have some great signs inside talking about serving up sarcasm and what not and I loved every bit of it.  You can order online, scam a QR code or order in person. Every biscuit sandwich we got was great. This is a must try if you ask me.', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/CBmAoXwrq9gCEhYBWULClQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Hot Link Bitchwich'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/n3G23-kYKJ4KzyrhWjHynA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Sausage Bitchwich'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/WS70FCJRjZLc2ym0JechDA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/z8pFKnggVeaEzf4E0lX6_g/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/jPrZZfoA9jCBJUjj-6rhSg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Bacon Bitchwich'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/qHC3pAejSPogTfsKSh9NYw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Iced Bitch Blend Drip Coffee'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Yk5kaRPlY8QxkAeXu6htPA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/s3DYRWOM8sKL_zpIyaNmew/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['8 photos']}, {'position': 10, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-03-21T02:33:34Z', 'user': {'name': 'Magda G.', 'user_id': 'I4OAlQm4B5XNOheSvK9lJw', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=I4OAlQm4B5XNOheSvK9lJw', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/Lm7doGysrtzYm7Fngqc0HQ/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Galt, CA', 'friends': 152, 'photos': 1853, 'reviews': 252, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': 'I've been wanted to try this spot because I read so many great reviews. I love biscuits so had to check it out. 
It's a small hole in the wall walk up spot where you order and pay. They do have signs that state it can take 15 minutes so "bitch wait"' lol. They are so welcoming and upbeat, it's infectious. They have music playing which is fun. They have merch showcasing against their store windows. 
I ordered the hot link bitchwich. It was just what I expected but better. It was so good!!!! The biscuit was crunchy, buttery, soft, and warm. The hot link had a nice touch of spice and egg with cheese. The others loved their bitchwich. They said it was sooo good! 
I highly recommend stopping here. I'm sure everything is amazing. Service is somtimes slow but it's not a big deal!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [], 'tags': []}, {'position': 3, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-27T06:06:13Z', 'user': {'name': 'Lillian C.', 'user_id': 'sILtiueheTi5Kc2gsMt4lA', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=sILtiueheTi5Kc2gsMt4lA', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/UPxHF8ps9JYJnFu_UnKG3A/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 263, 'photos': 65, 'reviews': 87, 'elite_year': 0}, 'comment': {'text': "This spot truly hit the spot, especially when going on an empt stomach.

Establishment - this place gets BUSY. There's a tablet by the front door that you can put your name down on a waitlist, and it gives you an estimate of how long it might take for your party to get called. My friends and I arrived around dinner time and it took us 15min to get a table, but the parties after us started seeing much longer wait times. The dining area overall is on the smaller side, with it being a long and narrow space with essentially two rows of tables. The way the space was decorated with the artwork on the walls and lanterns hanging above your heads made it feel chaotic but in the way that it might remind you of actually being in China, which yes, is a good thing (iykyk).

Service - wait staff was very friendly and I think they did a wonderful job of handling every customer during a hectic dinner rush. Our food also came out so fast that I was shocked. But, given that the restaurant specializes in this particular type of noodle, I wasn't surprised. 

Food - oh my gosh. This stuff was so, so good. If you're expecting egg noodles or rice noodles or anything you'd get from any other Chinese restaurant, think again. If you come to this restaurant, expect long and wide noodles that take multiple slurps and bites to finish. I think I counted maybe 5 pieces of these noodles, and quite frankly it was extremely filling. This spot is known for the spicy dishes, but they offer non-spicy too, which is what I ordered. The bowl is packed not only with this special noodle type, but the other contents in the bowl were outstanding. The meat just slid right off the bone. The soup was packed with veggies, and the half egg was a nice touch. The only critique I will give was that I felt the soup was a little too salty. But, given that I just finished a hike earlier that day, a bit of salt felt needed. On any other day, though, I'd maybe water it down just a touch.

The noodles were perfect, the mushrooms were flavorful, and the whole dish just felt great. 

I was sitting at the bar, and service was relatively fast and friendly. Definitely coming back to try more!', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [], 'tags': []}, {'position': 2, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-04-25T19:09:27Z', 'user': {'name': 'Connie C.', 'user_id': 'w3iXYLy7b89aoDxfU96i5g', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=w3iXYLy7b89aoDxfU96i5g', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/XYWcKhvHILq-iVaBkH2iZg/180s.jpg', 'address': 'San Bruno, CA', 'friends': 474, 'photos': 2589, 'reviews': 581, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "This was surprisingly good despite reading some reviews from my Yelp friends that they were disappointed, but those were from ages ago. I made a reservation ahead of time for a group of 5, so skipped out on needing to wait on the cold corner. The place is kind of small, just 2 chairs by the entrance for the waiting area, a bar right behind the host, and then packed tables in the back. We did family style with 5 people at a table suitable for 4, that felt a game of Tetris. 

We had one person in the group who was vegan so we tried out more of the non-meat dishes; they were surprisingly delicious. Usually I feel bad for vegetarians for their limited choices, but Kedai Mekan did not miss. There is a good spice level to the dishes, it's definitely a Southeast Asian mild. Generally not enough but I wanted something a bit more gentle for my traveler's stomach that night, so it was just right. We split two appetizers and two entrees, thinking we would need more, turns out we had leftovers. We got the mushroom pan mee, chicken wings, roti ajar, and nasi goreng. mushroom pan mee was our table's favorite. I'd go for a second if we were going for round 2. Roti ajar was a surprise, I had in mind was something like a flaky thin paratha, not this netted pancake. Don't get me wrong, it was good, the cashew curry sauce was also delicious. Nasi goreng had that right fried rice texture where Uncle Roger would be so proud. chicken wings were good but that was messy. If you don't want to use your hands at all, skip it.

I would definitely come back if I'm in town.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/YOWzc3tTmjMD6bfHTZ5PkQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Nasi goreng'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/UqwQr-UZf5Pi4YzT4wEV8g/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Fired chicken wings'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/3lDf5k9seNx-caowcopJjQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Roti ajar'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/P0UwH-PjFjfB-O0jprlPWg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Mushroom pan mee'}], 'tags': ['4 photos', 'Seated via Yelp Reservations', '1 check-in']}, {'position': 3, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-05T14:33:30Z', 'user': {'name': 'Kumar V.', 'user_id': 'v9xS9FCL7bR5zzqGG3lRPw', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=v9xS9FCL7bR5zzqGG3lRPw', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/J05jOdfwLBwQJSq-PNiV5Q/180s.jpg', 'address': 'WA, WA', 'friends': 35, 'photos': 948, 'reviews': 205, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': 'Jala roti with chicken curry - absolute heaven. Visited Capitol Hill for the day and this spot was conveniently near lots of the shops.

However, on my most recent visit (yesterday), I did notice the portions seemed a bit smaller. That said, the servings were still generous and shareable.

The ambiance is lovely--it's more of a sit-down vibe, perfect for a date night or hanging out with friends. The paper lantern and dim lighting created a cozy and romantic ambiance for dinner. Definitely recommend making a reservation ahead of time, especially on weekend nights when it tends to get busy.

As for the food, I thought a few of the main dishes leaned a bit on the sweeter side. I highly recommend the roti jala as an appetizer! The net-like bread has such a soft texture, and the chicken curry dipping sauce was rich and flavorful. Interestingly, the curry had a slight sweetness to it.

I also really enjoyed the nasi lemak, which came with coconut rice, your choice of tofu or chicken curry (same curry as the roti jala), and other tasty sides. The coconut rice was full of flavor. Another dish worth trying is the nasi goreng--a delicious fried rice dish!

The chili pan mee (wheat noodles with ground pork) was just okay for me. It felt like it was missing a little something in terms of seasoning.

The food came out quickly after we ordered, which was great. Just a heads-up: there's a mandatory 20% service charge, regardless of the party size.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/9u-Dyxv9IeWx9s3YQeV7yg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Roti Jala IG: michelleliphoto'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/SfGczfFv-y6BKhb_cZax8A/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Chili Pan Mee (top) and Nasi Lemak (bottom) IG: michelleliphoto'}], 'tags': ['2 photos']}]

name: Shaker + Spear
reviews_data:
[{'position': 1, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-05-04T13:07:57Z', 'user': {'name': 'Julia C.', 'user_id': 'Te2500DlCQz19D7isDv86A', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=Te2500DlCQz19D7isDv86A', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/NHpxF8EGwc1VjHsPMkXmIA/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Greenbelt, MD', 'friends': 757, 'photos': 353, 'reviews': 119, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Shaker + Spear in Seattle absolutely deserves this glowing 5-star review--this place is a standout in every way. From the moment we arrived, the service was warm and attentive without ever feeling rushed. The atmosphere is cozy and inviting, with just the right amount of energy for a memorable night out.

The meal started off on a high note with their house bread--fresh, warm, and served with a perfectly whipped butter that made it hard to stop at just one piece. We shared the fingerling potatoes as a side, and they were incredible: crispy on the outside, tender on the inside, and seasoned to perfection with just a touch of herb and salt that made them totally addictive.

The wine selection was impressive--well-curated and thoughtful, with options to suit every palate. Our server gave excellent pairing suggestions, and the glass of white I had went beautifully with the star of the show: the salmon. Cooked to absolute perfection, the salmon was tender, flavorful, and accompanied by a delicate balance of sides and sauces that elevated the entire dish. It was easily one of the best seafood plates I've had in Seattle.

Every detail felt intentional and elevated, from the food to the ambiance to the flawless service. If you're in Seattle and want a dining experience that feels both special and relaxed, Shaker + Spear should be at the top of your list. I can't wait to go back!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Q19fBQba6HWLctWT-IjaqA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/UTl9XvRO2F9-e-a0Pv2OVA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/hHoDVZ9FZfiXkVN_mXW1FA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/LR1xcRnoH2JhAxT8pcFbiA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Mt6uQ97VPXY7MCBOB7gc9A/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/OL1WaeyKNNYlgopPT8BxuA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['6 photos', '1 check-in']}, {'position': 2, 'rating': 3, 'date': '2025-05-03T17:29:53Z', 'user': {'name': 'Victoria S.', 'user_id': 'm8YRg68_52Vlj1tYYyC6Ug', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=m8YRg68_52Vlj1tYYyC6Ug', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/hN5404GhebAU7y6pMmHnMQ/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Jersey City, NJ', 'friends': 85, 'photos': 403, 'reviews': 200, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "This place was just ok. The hazelnut espresso martini was the best thing. The omelette was just ok. The potatoes were decent. Nothing had impeccable flavor. 

The servers were fast and I was grateful to have made a last minute reservation. It's a small quaint place.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/wmLsYSrsIqS8okev2rI-Rg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Brunch menu'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/sNjPUiJegegiFwLVF2ElKA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'French Chive Omelette'}], 'tags': ['2 photos', '1 check-in']}, {'position': 3, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-16T11:10:59Z', 'user': {'name': 'Sue F.', 'user_id': 'aY7AA4iGOh0GoV7IBwZoPQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=aY7AA4iGOh0GoV7IBwZoPQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/toJpSGZZAsHR2bN79uj8SA/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 0, 'photos': 3, 'reviews': 2, 'elite_year': 0}, 'comment': {'text': 'My husband and I visited Shaker + Spear for a  date night and left full and happy. 

We did not have a reservation but were warmly greeted by Zhilin, who managed to find us a table even during the busy dinner rush. She also took our coats which was a nice thoughtful touch. 

Our server Angie was wonderful. She was friendly, knowledgeable, and clearly passionate about the menu. She mentioned that the trout and scallops were house favorites. I decided on the trout, while my husband ordered the filet with scallops. Both dishes  were beautifully presented and  delicious. I am not usually a fan of sweet potatoes, but the puree that came with the trout worked well 

Our server also recommended a couple of drinks . I tried the Morticia Adams, and while I was hesitant  at  first because of the squid ink, it was subtle. The drink was sour, herbal, and really unique just like it was explained. My husband had the Spicy Maya, a whisky drink with peppers

The space is modern and minimalist with an open kitchen that adds some great energy without being too loud. Service throughout the night was quick, attentive, and genuinelly kind. 

My only small complaint is that oysters were not available, which felt a bit odd for a seafood-focused spot. But honestly, everything else more than made up for it

Highly recommend for a relaxed night out.', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/5MrztKOvgwHWvwA_fjXJRA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Trout'}], 'tags': ['1 photo']}, {'position': 4, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-05-04T03:24:21Z', 'user': {'name': 'Winter B.', 'user_id': 'JfT_TEVLrq48kg3XVaF37Q', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=JfT_TEVLrq48kg3XVaF37Q', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/_lsTG2DOzsP-kHWR3AnlmQ/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Eugene, OR', 'friends': 118, 'photos': 1603, 'reviews': 458, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': 'I came here for dinner tonight and had a really nice experience. like choices. 

We ordered the crab and avocado appetizer. It was pretty good. The avocado was fresh, however, the crab didn't seem as fresh as it could have been. This appetizer came with one medium sized chip, truly a fork and knife appetizer and very shareable with one other person. 

For the main course we ordered the Miso Black Cod and also the Filet. The Black Cod was delicious, but smaller in portion. The Miso "sauce" was delicious. The side dish was not amazing and not eaten. 

The Filet was surprising because it was larger in  portion, very enjoyable in flavor and also tasted organic and local. It was accompanied by broccolini and onion.

Shaker and Spear offers a fairly extensive wine menu. 

For dessert, we chose the gelato and it was yummy. 

The service was attentive.

After we were seated, we began exploring the menu. The menu is one-page, but I like the intention behind all the details. My partner asked about possible modifications and we received feedback directly from the chef, who implemented our preferences into our plates.

reviews_data:
[{'position': 1, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-03-16T02:28:30Z', 'user': {'name': 'Fernando C.', 'user_id': 'XWGMuH_hnr01J10uX2WtSQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=XWGMuH_hnr01J10uX2WtSQ', 'thumbnail': '', 'address': 'Bothell, WA', 'friends': 0, 'photos': 0, 'reviews': 1, 'elite_year': 0}, 'comment': {'text': 'Steaks are amazing, great environment and food arrive very fast and with high quality.

Should try their Delmonico!!', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [], 'tags': ['Seated via Yelp Reservations']}, {'position': 2, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-23T21:16:27Z', 'user': {'name': 'Khanh H.', 'user_id': '4jehKOYfQKPeetywYhMz8A', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=4jehKOYfQKPeetywYhMz8A', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/xC1gaIWh7LiqGrUofsMzxg/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 638, 'photos': 351, 'reviews': 127, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Writing this review for specifically our server Emily! She was amazing! I loved that she didn't try to sell us on things just to make our bill higher, she was honestly and said 3 potatoes would be too much for our group which we really appreciated the honestly. When the food came out it was pretty crowded with the hot stones and just all of us at the table so she helped us maneuver some of the stones to the middle and take away the extra. I just thought that was SO thoughtful and that was just above and beyond service. We love her and her energy!

As for the food, we have been so many times and it is always so delicious. Get the Zabuton and you will not be disappointed!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/pS9hQyzvf3YZyPlmutLOJQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Papa josper (Insta: @badtothebite)'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/4TPDYwu2wr8tinB41-wPjQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'El Zabuton (Insta: @badtothebite)'}], 'tags': ['2 photos', 'Seated via Yelp Reservations']}, {'position': 3, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-20T17:00:25Z', 'user': {'name': 'Tiffany G.', 'user_id': 'u8CFTz7h3F-8IXm34x707A', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=u8CFTz7h3F-8IXm34x707A', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/bSLAiHV8C6hFNCCxrrHt9Q/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Hartford, CT', 'friends': 521, 'photos': 4126, 'reviews': 338, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Omg!!! I'm picky. Those that know me and even those that love me, would be shocked to hear me announce I was in heaven while eating my Filet Mignon Flight! 

It was perfectly cooked, service was good, and you get a hot stone and 3 sauces to go with? It was too good to even risk letting any of the filets get cold so I focused on them and barely touched the sides to work on the amazing Japanese and Australian beef in front of me! 

We were only in Seattle for a few days before our Alaskan cruise, and one day after, and I convinced the hubby to come back after our cruise, for that one last day! Literally can't say enough good things,  it's small and the vibe is right, and it's not cheap but oh it's worth every single penny! Great spot!!! Phenomenal. Like. I would use my skymiles to fly across the country just to come back here!!!

My favorite wings are in Oakdale, Minnesota (D Spot) and my favorite steak in the US is HERE!!!!! And if you're here in Seattle on a weekend, GO get the ube pancakes at Ludi's! Foodie heaven over here!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 3, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 3}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Vjre0VZxRazPFn23cmUU3g/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Yes, give me that flight!'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Qq2F06uvGVRoSy5Hw3H9tQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Oh yeah, getting ready for the food.'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ivFFJKTZZOWqL_rv4blYig/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Me and my flight!'}], 'tags': ['3 photos']}, {'position': 4, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-09T18:42:12Z', 'user': {'name': 'Robert S.', 'user_id': 'XhCHuP_fjtN1TdYIByncwA', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=XhCHuP_fjtN1TdYIByncwA', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/YjD10pJxyCxosoyAWlelFw/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Kirkland, WA', 'friends': 127, 'photos': 26, 'reviews': 72, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Took my wife to Asadero for her birthday and I'm glad we did! We've been wanting to go here for months but never had the chance because of availability. 

We started with the guacamole which came with tortillas and bread to dip. The guacamole was nothing special but that's what made it good! We used the sauces and pickled onions that they provide to add to the flavor of the guacamole. My wife got the NY strip on the hot stone with a side of rice. They asked her to check doneness before she started eating to make sure it was cooked perfectly, which we appreciated. I got the  Parilla Sonora which came with American wagyu, beans, and an Anaheim chile relleno. It was delicious! Both steaks had the perfect seasoning, but with the hot stones it over cooked. Especially my American wagyu because they were thinner slices. I'd recommend getting the steak cooked a bit less than you normally would then let the stone cook it to your liking. 

For dessert, my wife got the arroz con leche and I got the flan flight. Both desserts were really good. The flan flight came with a corn flan, a chocolate flan, and a cheesecake like flan. At the end of the meal, they bring you some tea to help digest your food. 

Overall, we loved Asadero and their great service. We now understand why it's always booked when we try to go. We will definitely be back to try other menu items.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/khtbhb7dgp7HNE3EKeRO0g/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['1 photo', 'Seated via Yelp Reservations']}, {'position': 5, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-03-05T15:59:31Z', 'user': {'name': 'Ananya J.', 'user_id': '1cxy-vrx-vW37t2WvhIHoA', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=1cxy-vrx-vW37t2WvhIHoA', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/jBkE9_BBNBx7fDAef608vA/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 4, 'photos': 58, 'reviews': 32, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Had an absolutely lovely time at Asadero this Monday! We were promptly seated as per our reservation. We were then presented with a selection of citrus and additions we could customize our water with. Great touch and way to set the tone of the meal. 

We ordered the guacamole to start and then 3 main dishes and a baked potato to share for 4. 

The guacamole was good! Straightforward, well seasoned. No complaints. It came with bread and crackers. I think it also came with an array of salsas. Unsure whether that accompanied the guac or the meal. But we needed the salsa to finish the bread/crackers. Guac was fully consumed since we came hungry.

The steaks arrived next. Our server answered all our questions before and after serving about our steaks. We ordered the Vasio medium and the El Zabuton medium rare. We took it off the sizzle plate once they came to stop the cooking. The Vasio was our favorite steak of the night. We needed to add salt but were provided rock salt so it was a bit tricky. Salsas provided were great in enhancing and complimenting the flavor of the meat.

The baked potato was a bit of a let down for me since I got to it mid-steak and the cheese had congealed. It didn't enhance my experience much. 

The Carne Asada was okay! There were tortillas provided that seemed handmade. Great light texture. The meat was decent but since it was so thin, it's at risk of getting a bit tough. There was a lot of meat on that plate too, good portion but compared to the steaks, this was not the star of the night. If you get this one as your only main, it's a good pick. 

All in all, loved the service, ambience and food. We sat for a while as we picked off the remaining bites of food and never felt rushed by service. Would come again for that Vasio and assortment of salsas!!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_wSnEWnQ9zkh0n_HE_RxfA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Carne Asada'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/4A08x9FpP1h5rfGsYUx0AQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Guacamole'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/uf93ew06-1YMVnja3Wtg8Q/o.jpg', 'caption': 'El Zabuton'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/CvBjIgaF_rzjhnYp5elfEw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Papa Joseph'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/T1BF-CLM9FhHihQsGnGr1w/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Salsas'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Ck316rfcP_mdtgJxIjWXyg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Vacio'}], 'tags': ['6 photos']}, {'position': 6, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-01-23T01:15:54Z', 'user': {'name': 'Tribecca B.', 'user_id': 'N_L-enlz4PoQimwsHI96oA', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=N_L-enlz4PoQimwsHI96oA', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/MbMKz1G2eJD3GNxifp9v7A/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Mountlake Terrace, WA', 'friends': 11, 'photos': 187, 'reviews': 99, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': 'Still love this place! I was curious to know what a Mexican steakhouse was going to be like but it was everything my Mexican heart desires! Great cuts of meat, spicy salsa, fresh ingredients, prompt service and very helpful stuff and intimate setting.

We went yesterday for my husbands bday and we're sat right away. From the start it was a special experience. We both ordered the stuffed jalapeños to start and the guac as well which was simple and delicious. I hate when people try to over complicate guacamole and this was just how I like it.

We both ordered the 39od  bone in NY and each of ours were cooked to perfection. We split the papa loca and the rajitas and we were so stuffed! 

Andrea was our server and she made such great recommendations and always made sure our wine glasses were full. Thank you Andrea!

We liked it so much we made another reservation for MY birthday in 3 weeks!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [], 'tags': ['Seated via Yelp Reservations']}, {'position': 8, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-01-11T01:39:31Z', 'user': {'name': 'Rick Smitz ..', 'user_id': 'rx4EwQjJacuR4jqIQ1kFwQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=rx4EwQjJacuR4jqIQ1kFwQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/7Q7qfQLKQAd-2_d3nnV0yg/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 5, 'photos': 172, 'reviews': 57, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "To sum up the experience of dining at this establishment.... Amazing! 
The ambiance is very comfortable and welcoming, yet small enough for a personal touch. 
The Waygu selections are incredible and perhaps has become one of my new favorite date spots! 
The servers are top notch and can walk you through the menu and answer any questions you might have. 
Plan to spend considerably more than the average meal, but after the first taste of a steak or waygu steak burger, you'll forget all about the cost and just enjoy incredible food.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/vmFLGZQogmSNImxCsONVqQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/TaJWAWo9BBMXYSoZMlPC-g/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_Bsiv248rC5CfxH5b-BfZg/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['3 photos']}, {'position': 9, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-01-05T00:47:11Z', 'user': {'name': 'karthik', 'user_id': '_zYLSbOLkI3mH1fkk9VtxQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=_zYLSbOLkI3mH1fkk9VtxQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/egJ1VjO5KB1jAsZDAn-hhw/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Redmond, WA', 'friends': 1, 'photos': 12, 'reviews': 16, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': 'Amazing taste. 
The A5 wagu table side steak is must try. 

QUESO FUNDIDO CON CHORIZO was tasting great. 

Pleasant ambience. 
Great service. 
I would definitely recommend. 
Must try.', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/iFtHBLtvI1SmibvxhT4qsg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'A5 wagyu table side rib eye'}], 'tags': ['1 photo']}, {'position': 10, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2024-12-29T21:31:38Z', 'user': {'name': 'Lauren S.', 'user_id': 'wYmh1UspGCo0SFUxGLT14A', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=wYmh1UspGCo0SFUxGLT14A', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/KkorXDoNYxrtPgOfanoiWA/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Sacramento, CA', 'friends': 433, 'photos': 63, 'reviews': 93, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': 'We had a reservation for 7:45 on a Friday night and it was full when we arrived! The place is dimly lit, wood table/booths and you can kind of see into the kitchen area. 

They start off with pouring you water and then they bring around this large wood board with lemon, lime, mint, and cucumber and give you the option to add any of it to your water. I thought this was great! What an easy thing to do that really goes a long way for the customer. 

We started with the queso which came with "chips" and soft tortillas. It was a huge appetizer, more than enough for all 4 of us. They also bring around 2 different kinds of salsa, pickled onions, and pico de gallo. We took our time ordering we were enjoying our time together and they never made us feel rushed. 

Two of us ordered the fish tacos which were delicious, while the other two ordered the Japanese Wagyu and the American Wagyu. Our waiter was super knowledgeable and explained a lot about how there can be American Wagyu, where the cows come from, etc. The japanese Wagyu comes raw and then they bring you an individual hot stone to cook it on, they even brought a second one once the first wasn't as hot anymore. 

Overall it was an amazing experience and would definitely recommend!', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/uP__is2Y93WzSuQN_USFlA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Japanese Wagyu'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/6FGJevQPvT94P5fkQKppSg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Fish tacos'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/5VnbuKETa5s3whs5xCT3hQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'American Wagyu'}], 'tags': ['3 photos']}]

name: Chan Seattle
reviews_data:
[{'position': 1, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-29T13:55:08Z', 'user': {'name': 'Calista C.', 'user_id': 'gLD9t4knR-UJVWfv4UYO2Q', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=gLD9t4knR-UJVWfv4UYO2Q', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/0QhBo9y52TMS3TMMdlkLvQ/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 236, 'photos': 291, 'reviews': 97, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Came here for Seattle Restaurant Week!

All the food was delicious! Highly recommend the wagyu ssam, brussel sprouts, and the ginger crème brûlée! Even though I don't like ginger, the crème brûlée didn't taste strongly of ginger and was the best thing I had all night. Unfortunately, their black sesame cheesecake was sold out before we could order dessert but all the other desserts we tried were amazing so I'm assuming it was just as good !! Would come back just for the desserts! The smoked duck sotbap was a little lacking and oily with no crispy rice - the only item we didn't love.

Service was friendly and the restaurant is perfect for a date night.

The bathroom is in the hotel, needing a keycard and an elevator ride which is a little inconvenient.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/P4tVKk1iVaABJT89gyHxsw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Steak Tartare'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/5d4s5y98m4FqFPUvqy8CTg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'American Wagyu Ssam'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/AKvOnp2hmK_MSmRdeQgCPA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Smoked Duck Sotbap'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/TptLtgkbeVa1GQPxvxla6A/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Brussel Sprouts'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/zvRcBh-Y2pqdu3-Iy2ZBrg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Ginger Creme Brulee and Caramel Creme'}], 'tags': ['5 photos']}, {'position': 2, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-04-12T18:27:51Z', 'user': {'name': 'Lynzette R.', 'user_id': 'T69skBM5fe5c5Ynk6PcVjQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=T69skBM5fe5c5Ynk6PcVjQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/Ww33rf1GuhVZ4CBbPMhxNg/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 1, 'photos': 32, 'reviews': 15, 'elite_year': 0}, 'comment': {'text': "appetizer: i didn't really care about the steak tartare and it was served with a cracker? it was interesting but the spicy pork slider was delicious! - 3/5 stars

entree: the smoked duck petit sotbap was so good and savory. im not a big fan of how they cooked the rice (a bit mushy) the pork jowl was incredibly tender. it also came with pearl barley which i never had before.. it was alright but the meat itself was yummy. - 4/ 5 stars

dessert: black sesame basque cheese cake and caramel custard was a cherry on top and i love how it's not too sweet! - 5/5 stars", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/7H380N2cJpEg7eN9rPYbuA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/oPTFXKY2awwnp2Hg27p0vw/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/gpr-UR0ZwSi0UBb-7r8GHQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['3 photos']}, {'position': 3, 'rating': 3, 'date': '2025-04-10T22:43:17Z', 'user': {'name': 'Yegee L.', 'user_id': 'XWPFBTc-GCPhS6Eb17STYw', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=XWPFBTc-GCPhS6Eb17STYw', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/pOEiAr5qROEltpQKbuLfYw/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 311, 'photos': 222, 'reviews': 107, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "I really like the ambience of the restaurant. The  Korean style floor mats are a nice touch, and practical (as they make the benches comfortable to sit on). Their ceramics are very eye catching, and some are reminiscent of Korean style ceramics. There's touches of Korean influence as well as a feeling of modernity. 

The food was a hit or a miss. I think the presentation and taste of the steak tartare was a little underwhelming. But the brusselsprouts, were crispy, sweet, and savory. I really enjoyed the flavor of the brusselsprouts appetizer. 

The duck sotbap was buttery, addicting. We initially forgot to add/mix the gochujang into the dish and thought initially that while buttery it was a bit bland. But once we added the gochujang, it was well seasoned and the flavors played well together. 

The lobster ramen, however, was quite bland. The lobster itself was well seasoned and sizable. But the noodles and soup could've been better seasoned. It wasn't deep in flavor either. 

The star of the show was definitely the desserts. If I could come back for the desserts only I would. 

The ginger crème brûlée from the description sounds a bit weird. But the ginger is subtle, and I couldn't taste dwenjang in the caramel. All the flavors combine well to produce a sweet and creamy dish. It doesn't have that caramelized hardened shell that I was expecting but it was delicious. 

The black sesame is nutty, and not very sweet. It's got a bit of crumbly texture but it is a good compliment to the vanilla ice cream.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/tZuJ8qfrN5PqzKwW9CnYkg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Steak Tartare'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/EX72rtNniC0lBBBIbQvPxg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Ginger Creme Brulee'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/VMnKByuttcfgtxgnJIQi2w/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Black sesame cheesecake'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/YS7iVzsyBtUpA_kYEOMRXQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Fried brusselsprouts'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/NPiGsDJFBXidRLwq1nDNOw/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Duck sotbap, lobster ramen'}], 'tags': ['5 photos', '1 check-in']}, {'position': 4, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-04-09T04:35:29Z', 'user': {'name': 'Alex V.', 'user_id': '_yZ79_PNJJ1iptP1GpL7tA', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=_yZ79_PNJJ1iptP1GpL7tA', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/toKHIERORc7bzuMDDtHmHw/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 9, 'photos': 135, 'reviews': 119, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "My friend and I went to Chan Seattle for Restaurant Week and had a great time. To start, the place is warm and modern. For appetizers, my friend and I split the steak tartare and fire-roasted cauliflower - both were packed with flavor and presented nicely.

For entrées, the pork jowl was incredibly tender, and the smoked duck bap was savory although I thought it was a little dry.

Since I don't have a huge sweet tooth, the dessert was impressive: the black sesame cheesecake was nutty and not too sweet, while the ginger crème brûlée had a perfect spice-to-sweet balance. Additionally, their espresso martini had a nice cinnamon finish, which was a fun twist.

Our waiter was super attentive and friendly - great service all around. Highly recommend for a flavorful, well-rounded dining experience!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/7balodE7d5rZeRE37ZKBMA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Fire roasted cauliflower'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/2rRE9bfwjmUNmjkMs37QcQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Tartare'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/75d7yffLNhx2EhCQS4pW-w/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Black sesame cheesecake'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/p_hsg1aEp-cjcvoiElRlMg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Pork jowl'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/4uEjx8PAMlI6cOmHv7z9TA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Ginger Creme Brulee'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/jIf58pXPYnx3sW13zkY7_w/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Duck'}], 'tags': ['6 photos']}, {'position': 5, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-09T00:24:56Z', 'user': {'name': 'Flora L.', 'user_id': 'RhumBf8pXq3nv-oaPlw6FQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=RhumBf8pXq3nv-oaPlw6FQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/0pwo-CGKhaZeNY62F2S-Ww/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 327, 'photos': 1068, 'reviews': 244, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Came for restaurant week but ended up doing happy hour deals! Happy hour is such a great deal. The appetizers are $10 and cocktail is $10.

Beef tartar: omg a MUST! It was so good that we ordered 3 of it. It's perfection. Beef is fresh and comes with pine nuts, Korean pear, drizzled in sesame oil, and within the crunchy thin rice flour (in Korean/Japanese, it's called Monaka) 

Tuna tartar: not as yummy as beef tartar but still good! Comes with avocado pieces.

Fried chicken: wow didn't expect it to be so crunchy and juicy! Comes with pickled radish.

Beef sliders: this one was just okay. There weren't too much meat. The bread was too thick. Lacked flavor. 

Cauliflower: wow wow wow. Please get this dish. This dish has a burst of flavors.

Duck dolsot bap: rice topped with duck and comes with red peppered radish (kkak ttu gi) and pickled radish as banchans along with seaweed and gochujang. The rice was cooked to al dante which i like but I wouldn't get this again. It wasn't too special for me.

1000% I'd come back. Service was fast and attentive. Bathroom is upstairs inside the hotel so ask for the bathroom keycard to use it. The interior was modern and inviting.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_CJ79xELk1CyX2luDVHqCQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/l-vdKYE-ODg3AKsWZh-LbQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/svZ52VYTZu_ieWsUlfU73Q/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/PuAztq17FWB3wHl4EGMz_A/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/5zJcEyGzYFTJ6XlA9-Q4_Q/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Wq-FDaA52jR0RVwvLr-j6g/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/OzlE3aR_XOsYSkutkVdemw/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/G-KDd2ixYppasD5XOu7NmA/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ZKr07xv9aoJJIb9PtEpvgg/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/aBbUfx8unzk1UssoH0zvow/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['10 photos', '1 check-in']}, {'position': 6, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-03-15T18:27:41Z', 'user': {'name': 'Nora J.', 'user_id': '_fFXs6J3zrC4GeNF14EwOQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=_fFXs6J3zrC4GeNF14EwOQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/iiX0ostKCHMaLOKhW77nvg/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 9, 'photos': 313, 'reviews': 172, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Decent Korean fusion restaurant in the Denny Triangle area! Came on a Friday night at 8pm and wasn't too busy (made a reservation about an hour in advance).
We got the beef sliders, steak tartare, brussel sprouts, beef brisket rice cake, and smoked duck.
The sliders were a bit disappointing because they were so tiny for how expensive they are. The steak tartare was alright but the cracker(?) they served it with had the texture of styrofoam. The brussel sprouts were one of my favorite things! The duck was good but the dish has a lot of rice and don't think it was worth it for $40.
The service was alright. They messed up our order three times but they were nice about it.
The food was decent and think this place is worth trying once but I don't think I'd come again.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/v4jEtGMlWS9cRDMOBix28Q/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/F7J1Vc5WMo9yln-Ip7tA2w/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/iOL26iY3HGZAIqvgaToY7g/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Y7ZSGwgVqz1p8cLfNR6aEg/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/6b6IBaEJ7JbQ0xcGTr6-xQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/4B_TnIJIpQU4LdEtcOoZIQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['6 photos']}, {'position': 7, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-15T20:06:28Z', 'user': {'name': 'Andrew T.', 'user_id': 'yqJLKjQzh9fZnAAPEaRRpw', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=yqJLKjQzh9fZnAAPEaRRpw', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/EcvgJz_wwBNZ1aHUU78IrA/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 23, 'photos': 171, 'reviews': 87, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': 'Even though we had a larger party service and food were impeccable. I ordered the smoked duck soft bap and it was enough the share with another person the duck was both tender and flavorful and not overcooked. Loved Chan Seattle and will go again!', 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/zo3sPldIR5lX3vu5CGMFcw/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['1 photo']}, {'position': 8, 'rating': 3, 'date': '2025-03-12T17:06:33Z', 'user': {'name': 'Ananya J.', 'user_id': '1cxy-vrx-vW37t2WvhIHoA', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=1cxy-vrx-vW37t2WvhIHoA', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/jBkE9_BBNBx7fDAef608vA/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 4, 'photos': 58, 'reviews': 32, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "I had really high hopes for this place but walked away disappointed. 

I'd say a highlight was service. Our waitress was energetic and attentive. We were seated near the kitchen in a hallway area and while it was fine, can't say much about ambiance since we weren't in the most lively area of the restaurant with other guests. 

We ordered two cocktails. 
- Passport to Paradise (3/5 - not bad, not spectacular) 
- Keopi Island Tuner (5/5 - very coffee forward though!)

Here's our order:
- Crispy Rice Salad (1/5) - I was soooo sad when this came to our table. I love a crispy rice salad but this was so simple and plain. It was a generic salad with some puffed rice with absolutely no flavor or dressing. This needs improvement. 
- Roasted Wagyu Bone Marrow (3.5/5) - I don't have a lot of experience eating bone marrow but I enjoyed this. Good chimichurri and lots of butter -  but the bone marrow didn't shine in this dish. A small pinch of salt would've brought out that flavor more? 
- Alaskan Salmon Sot Bap - (3.5/5) Since it was a Sot Bap, I expected the rice to get a little crispy on the bottom. Texturally, this didn't amaze me. Nothing tasted bad, I just expected more at the price point. Kimchi was provided and so was a sauce. This dish needed the sauce. It just lacked a little flavor but that leans toward the simplicity of Sot Baps. 

Maybe my expectations were higher given the vibe and reviews of the restaurant but I was let down. Next time I'll try some of the more classic and popular dishes and see if that changes anything.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/hZsmrTVlPvPCUb6R60-f-g/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Crispy Rice Salad'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/QP-JX_iVNHRsPAmDskqyzA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Sot Bap'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/3pI2ifB3C7rvrgrATnSBEw/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/0E7rLWy-yQExO4n9Qkl8eg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Bone Marrow'}], 'tags': ['4 photos']}, {'position': 9, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-02-19T02:57:56Z', 'user': {'name': 'Alisa Q.', 'user_id': 'EnNkoUaUpAeHxjszzQ9WNQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=EnNkoUaUpAeHxjszzQ9WNQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/YlV_PXrMv_d3GSn6yEmAlA/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Bothell, WA', 'friends': 5, 'photos': 85, 'reviews': 150, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Pricey, but worth it! The ingredients were top notch and the flavors were well curated. Great cocktails. Loved the rice we ordered and the lobster ramen too.  Together -- those 2 things were a sufficient portion to share for two adults. 

Service was fine and the construction makes it challenging to access restrooms. We arrived on time for our resy but still had to wait, this wasn't a huge deal but could be inconvenient if we were on a tighter schedule.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/C3YF7k_ZGypmYBzkI7ruTg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Lobster ramen special'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/d59cc42RdmcR8h7tshOSag/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Rice with beef (to share for 2)'}], 'tags': ['2 photos']}, {'position': 10, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-21T18:19:49Z', 'user': {'name': 'Fumie W.', 'user_id': 'RgEADn4JXKqTjIRyzGvD9A', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=RgEADn4JXKqTjIRyzGvD9A', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/YchrWnmJJVSUOSvV2xaU1g/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 24, 'photos': 536, 'reviews': 179, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "ohmygosh such a great date spot! came in for Seattle Restaurant Week, they had a 3 course $50 pp deal running. we tried the steak tartare, fire roasted king prawn, american wagyu SSAM, and smoked duck petit sotbap. the highlight of the night was the steak tartare and smoked duck petit sotbap. the dessert we tried was okay, personally don't think black sesame and cheesecake does not pair well. nonetheless the service and food was great! make sure to make reservations, this spot is popular. will be coming back!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/zy9DBKLj3_Z3AbcFw9gPMg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Ginger Creme Brulee and black sesame cheesecake'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/MLZE9XK9fUIZdIaFgfQtdg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Steak Tartare'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/BtMWQdWfedybgJD-ATEVAg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'fire roasted king prawns'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/cGuuwkePkAg1LE4UO5SMpg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'smoked duck petit sotbap'}], 'tags': ['4 photos', '1 check-in']}]
