reviews_data:
[{'position': 1, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-04-16T16:30:15Z', 'user': {'name': 'Green A.', 'user_id': 'kc6NDu4zMJ_vCM8LOKWP0g', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=kc6NDu4zMJ_vCM8LOKWP0g', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/v1cph8hFjr97lw0f9QyTeA/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 4, 'photos': 168, 'reviews': 61, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "One of my favorite restaurants in Seattle! We came here twice for New Years Eve and birthday celebration, and the food was consistently amazing! I think this place has the best Korean fusion food out of Seattle, LA, SF, and NY. 

We loved the braised short rib nori taco and sujebi bolognese. The short rib was so tender and flavorful - it is very expensive for the portion, but we got it during both of our visits with no regrets. Sujebi bolognese has such a unique texture from the sujebi - i would say it is not the same texture as traditional sujebi, but more like rice cake texture that soaks up the delicious sauce. 

We also loved their special, which was perilla truffle noodles - an elevated take on the Korean traditional perilla makgguksu. Their bingsoo dessert is a perfect way to end the meal - very light and refreshing! 

I think the service could be more friendly but with this kind of food, it doesn't bother me. The place is darkly lit, cozy, and clean. I'd save this for a special occasion!", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/j_0KY10sMc2z6upRXy40Kw/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/xGN7s4u1S7oNvwNEDxWTuQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/hKC_AipltHwejfm9se9eSQ/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ZcX0lkWzCUPSTQFHMiMiFg/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/gR7NSd2022TXEdr3C2Pnzw/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/81Uxpb86jDNXNIaNmesy-g/o.jpg', 'caption': ''}], 'tags': ['6 photos']}, {'position': 2, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-04-24T16:14:36Z', 'user': {'name': 'Wendy K.', 'user_id': 'nfL3ilIVq58nvT1iqS_ZpQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=nfL3ilIVq58nvT1iqS_ZpQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/w34WSPM37mnt8TAOvcumpA/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 246, 'photos': 5288, 'reviews': 834, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "Saving a star for full dining. dropped in a few nights ago was going to an event and needed to waste sometime so ordered a couple items off the happy hour menu. The cheesy corn and I asked the bartender what the popular drink was she suggested the vesper. She also suggested the house-made rice chips to go with the corn. Everything was delicious corn comes out piping hot and sizzling in a cast iron pan. the vesper was a beautifully balanced cocktail ice cold would definitely get that one again and was $2 during HH. 

I dealt mostly with the bartender during my visit can't say enough about the service friendly helpful and didn't make me feel rushed but still attentive. 

The space is beautiful, very open lots of windows. Much of the final touches to dishes are done in an open area in front of house which is cool to see. 

Excited to visit with a group pf people to try more of the menu and have an actual dinner.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 2, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/n-4GM-4K1Odw0ni1hV3ytg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Veper on Happy Hour Menu'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/MwIlMDpAq8ZiKvLs_bg4iQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Interior'}], 'tags': ['2 photos']}, {'position': 3, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-03-04T23:38:34Z', 'user': {'name': 'Yegee L.', 'user_id': 'XWPFBTc-GCPhS6Eb17STYw', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=XWPFBTc-GCPhS6Eb17STYw', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/pOEiAr5qROEltpQKbuLfYw/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 311, 'photos': 222, 'reviews': 107, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': "I don't often like fusion/re-imagined Korean food. I find that it's not often well executed or it just doesn't fit my palate. But Paju was such a delightful dining experience that it made me open to re-exploring cuisines like this. 

I think the octopus and the squid ink fried rice was good but not standout. The squid ink fried rice was flavorful, mainly tasted of the seaweed garnish, and surprisingly large in portion. 

My favorites were the beef tartare and the sujebi. The beef tartare had a surprisingly light flavor that, creamy and slightly sweet, which paired well with the deep umami flavor of the crispy seaweed. I felt that the sujebi mixed different elements together successfully. The crunchiness of the garnish w/ the chewiness of the sujebi. The meatiness of the bolognese w: the freshness of the pear. I couldn't stop eating this dish.

Paju's staff did their best to accommodate which I can appreciate but why change without communication? We were able to have the chef replace a key main and with another dish, but I was also a little put off by the fact that they gave us an ultimatum to either continue with the menu or substitute for both of us. Why would we choose an option that he can't eat? I do understand that the question was asked out of courtesy but it was unnecessary. Just tell us that both of us will be accommodated for the allergy.

Regardless, the menu was studded with some true gems that were absolutely dreamy like that caviar and egg amuse, the foie gras pearl barley, our off-menu dry aged ribeye, and the proper chocolate soufflé! Each dish had a kiss of Korean or Asian flair but I would say that most preparation did lean French so keep that in mind if you were expecting some of the stronger Korean flavors to show up.

All in all, the experience was intimate, elevated, and still a treat despite the snafu. I had two places in mind and decided to give Paju a try for my mom's birthday trip to Seattle. 

It was a Friday night around 6PM, to my surprise it was a bit quiet. We were seated right away, I was also very surprised to see that the chef was greeting guests, it's a pleasant surprise! 

Disappointingly, I didn't feel like we were very welcomed in the restaurant, just ... cold and quiet HAHA onto the food! 

Octopus: My friend recommended I try this dish and it was delicious. The octopus was cooked nicely, the dashima beurre blanc *chef's kiss* almost licked the dish 

Hamachi Crudo with Nengmyun broth: I was debating between this dish and the steak tartare; with a little encouragement from the server we decided on the yellowtail and I am glad I did! It was a very familiar taste but with unfamiliar combinations? The nengmyun broth and yellowtail harmoniously balanced each other; not one overwhelming the other. 

Mushrooms: I do not care what you say this is by far the BEST FREAKING thing I ate in Seattle. Please keep in mind this is my review and this is my opinion hehe I LOVED everything about this dish. Literally a flavor festival inside your mouth. Really enjoyed the kimchi inside that gave a punch of tang. I .. took it togo to eat it at the hotel ... HAHHA 

Bugak: I think this is a dish that can be loved by everybody. Korean elevated taco hehehe

Duck Special: This was not on the menu but was a special that night. The good was that the duck was cooked to perfection, it was pink with the skin nicely grilled and not chewy. It also came with a small side of duck...wellington? duck tarte? THAT was delicious! This dish comes with a few side banchans. 

Bingsu: I ... want to bring home a TUB of that ginger cream. Dear lawd I was so full but I couldn't stop eating it, I can bathe in that ginger cream HAHA 

Overall it was a great dinner. I'm not familiar with the history of Paju but it was just shy of perfection. Not sure what it was, everything was good and the restaurant was pretty but something was... off. 

We did get two glasses of wine, maybe I should've tried their cocktails.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 3, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 4}, 'photos': [{'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/XsvhYik6FU1EYMFrcOp4ig/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Inside'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/7wl7Sfh1oQOMMybL33f_Dg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Duck Special'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/QLnrUmbUGdErbrj7u93EWg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Octopus'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Dcq-BAu0Mry1IoBZEe8OWQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Bugak'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/J34k-R8O6u3y1oA9LMhTCg/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Mushroom'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/edsGxMyGKGp0nLcEc_HdzA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Bingsu'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/EQqC8JlQeTNeUcTUzCPwNA/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Yellowtail'}, {'link': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/pqDS8Wt953pJ_AipZD3ALQ/o.jpg', 'caption': 'Exterior'}], 'tags': ['8 photos']}, {'position': 7, 'rating': 5, 'date': '2025-02-24T03:27:49Z', 'user': {'name': 'Matt S.', 'user_id': 'ObWIruGdfvyFYhdMLdGatA', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=ObWIruGdfvyFYhdMLdGatA', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/7hZEIHQfoV2X9Gj_7DTETg/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 11, 'photos': 892, 'reviews': 224, 'elite_year': 25}, 'comment': {'text': 'We came to Paju on a Friday at around 4:45 just in time before Happy Hour ended at 5p. Beverages, Mule ($13HH), Amber ale (HH), and the Drunk Dial ($16).
Food: cheesy grits($10), chefs bbq platter ($34). 

Drinks were lovely and the chefs platter comes with three types of meat, two roasting sides, we had beans and yummy cornbread as our sides. 

This place gets really busy and loud and they rotate their tables really well and staff is amazing and kind.", 'language': 'en'}, 'feedback': {'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0}, 'photos': [], 'tags': []}, {'position': 4, 'rating': 4, 'date': '2025-01-29T19:59:34Z', 'user': {'name': 'Zoltan U.', 'user_id': '3G_zHzmxYf2jj4MtQG3XXQ', 'link': 'https://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=3G_zHzmxYf2jj4MtQG3XXQ', 'thumbnail': 'https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/photo/fUn1UdG5Y1r2APalecCqjg/180s.jpg', 'address': 'Seattle, WA', 'friends': 1, 'photos': 1, 'reviews': 11, 'elite_year': 0}, 'comment': {'text': 'The food and drinks here are very good, but I am quite annoyed at the service. To preface, I worked as a line cook for 6 years so I know what the job is like and what is a valid complaint from the customer.

I went in and sat at the counter. As soon as the bartender came up I informed him I was in a rush, ordered a sandwich to-go and a drink for while I wait. He was very friendly and prompt with the drink. Sitting at the counter I saw into the kitchen and noticed all the kitchen staff were just restocking condiments and the steam table (it was slow at the time, there were maybe 2 other tables that already had food). I didn't say anything because maybe there was someone cooking mine in the back, IDK. It was a full 10 minutes after my order before someone began cooking my food. I told the bartender to cancel the food and I'll pay for the drink since I didn't have time for this and he goes "Uhhh, well, we already started cooking your food", so I had to be late if I wanted the food I had to pay for. 

I want to give them another try because the food was good, but the staff made me miss an apointment so others angry at me and low-key ruined my afternoon.
